$ %PUBLIC%

The directory pointed at with the enviornment variable `%PUBLIC%` is used to store the data of the public user profile (which is accessible to all users on the system).

Usually, `%PUBLIC%` points to `→ Windows/dirs/Users[C:\Users]\Public`.

The exact location of this directory is stored in the → Windows/registry[registry] under
`→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows-NT/CurrentVersion/ProfileList` in the value `Public`.
